name: A KIND OF SELFISHNESS
description: This is part of a conceptual series called Obscure Times that describes depression disease. Depression is an alteration of the tone of mood to forms of deep sadness with reduced self-esteem and self-serving need. Depending on the psychoanalytic interpretation, depression would be the reaction to the real or imaginary loss of the beloved object introjected by the subjectâ€™s ego and toward which feelings of hatred begin with the consequent guilty feelings and reproaches of the Super- I.
